title.narrative: Elimination of malaria in Honduras through the implementation of DTIR and comprehensive approach in targeted areas

description.narrative: Honduras - Malaria - Cooperative Housing Foundation - CHF. This program has the following goals: Zero indigenous malaria cases registered by 2020. The objectives of this program are: To promote integrated vector management. To strengthen the epidemiological strategy for malaria differentiated by strata and maintaining control of the emergence of outbreaks. To strengthen the coverage and quality of malaria diagnosis and treatment services. To strengthen the role of the Health System including the community role
